lse,"excerpt":"Al-Hakam ibn al-A\u2019raj reported: I went to Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, and I said, \u201cTell me about fasting the day of 'Ashura.\u201d Ibn Abbas said, \u201cWhen you see the crescent of the month of al-Muharram, count the days and wake up to fast on the ninth\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15090,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/16\/junub-before-fasting\/","url_meta":{"origin":15096,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: Waking up in major impurity before fasting","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 16, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would wake up at dawn in a state of major impurity, then he would perform a ritual bath and observe fasting. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1925, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1109 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11958,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/31\/wives-permission-husbands-sawm\/","url_meta":{"origin":15096,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: Wives need permission from husband to voluntarily fast","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 31, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cA woman should not fast in the presence of her husband except with his permission.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 4820, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1026 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim Al-Nawawi said, \u201cThe reason for\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27531,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/11\/prophet-connects-shaban-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":15096,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Sha\u2019ban: The Prophet fasts in Sha\u2019ban before Ramadan","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 11, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would fast until we said he will never break his fast, and he would not fast until we said he would never fast. I did not see the Prophet complete an entire month of fasting except for Ramadan,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":29046,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/10\/spouses-kissing-fasting\/","url_meta":{"origin":15096,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: Spouses kissing each other while fasting","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 10, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, leaned forward to kiss me. I said, \u201cI am fasting.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cAnd I am fasting,\u201d then he kissed me. Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 24861 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064e\u0627 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0647\u0652\u0648\u064e\u0649 \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15065,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/15\/prophet-hurry-break-fast\/","url_meta":{"origin":15096,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Siyam: The Prophet hastens to break his fast","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 15, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu 'Atiyyah reported: Masruq and I visited Aisha, may Allah be pleased with her, and he said, \u201cO mother of the believers, there are two companions of Muhammad and neither of them hold back from doing good. One of them hastens to break his fast and to perform the evening\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/15096","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https: